Socialist newspapers, magazines and books have seen their readership expand dramatically, along with the debate about how to win fundamental change.
As socialists, however, we would say that the working class is made up of the vast majority of people.
Socialists see the global working class, which is increasingly female-majority and multi-racial, as the key force to change the world.
For all these reasons the socialist movement needs to be international.
The lessons of this defeat must be learned by the workers and socialist movement internationally.